<file xmlns:its="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its" xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:qh5="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiv2p2_html5_v1p0">
    <sharedstimuli>
        <sharedstimulus id="assets/d67a0fbc639a4a7cbbd91/passage NEW.xml">
            <label key="d29cf2e263a7c9824dfe75afaf3af0fc">
                <text>Ice Stupas</text>
            </label>
            <label key="0ad8effd51d74075229b97e3dc74822f">
                <text>Ladakh is a high-altitude desert in northern India. Winter temperatures are well below freezing at night.  </text>
            </label>
            <label key="8c40d0374133412dddd0831c6d0ec5c5">
                <text>In the spring and summer, the villagers grow crops. In the past, villagers irrigated their crops using meltwater that trickled down from glaciers.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="7b7e9c713d25a1126841f4c57ce19745">
                <text>Glaciers have been shrinking in recent decades and there has not been enough water for irrigation in spring.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="faa7ae8ce4e6fe0425f729e8db083703">
                <text>To alleviate this problem, engineers have created artificial glaciers, called ice stupas, to capture meltwater during the winter.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="f7a6c63fba71bd74b3a003114578faa3">
                <text>An ice stupa consists of a conical framework of netting and thorn bushes. At night, a pipe sprays the framework with meltwater, which freezes. Over time, over 8 million litres of ice can accumulate. </text>
            </label>
            <label key="0a8c0ffece1fa6eb96f2614bd6827b3f">
                <text>In spring, the ice stupa begins to melt and provides water for the villagers and their crops.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="e8d881c9b4bc0cf92368df65b2197d92">
                <text>
                    <strong>glacier</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="491ce7926eec1d093a699f7e076a36f9">
                <text>
                    <strong>meltwater source</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="e9cff246658a835621e37351d992a151">
                <text>
                    <strong>pipe</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="850a02b20b64cc7d2c56834e5fd64078">
                <text>
                    <strong>ice stupa</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="523a9d8133e6b09e5b9568dfb1fa3788">
                <text>
                    <strong>river</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
            <label key="f4ade992e6592758f000ef1011234157">
                <text>
                    <strong>tap</strong>
                </text>
            </label>
        </sharedstimulus>
    </sharedstimuli>
    <items>
        <item id="i639a4b354f85c194587a6ac36ed8beba5f">
            <label key="31bf19036caff8e37b6ef0707ebb4f18">
                <text>Which one of the following forms of energy causes the water to spray over the ice stupa?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="02f4b0e8973dba14d25f39142fc78d4b">
                <text>chemical potential energy</text>
            </label>
            <label key="f3a96a880bbb3dab60f43bdf8898ff13">
                <text>thermal energy</text>
            </label>
            <label key="6e6ac1795560fe1b63f057465a770832">
                <text>gravitational potential energy</text>
            </label>
            <label key="5d7ededaaf7a34050a55035e4ddc9ffe">
                <text>light energy</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i639a4b4f435fd45906cb3cdfd6ef228edd">
            <label key="82c8f958e1bc8f2c617be8632c080856">
                <text>Salty water has a lower freezing point than pure water.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="a07c561e6df9b86b499e99ef78c2556b">
                <text>Given this information, Saha made a suggestion.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="604190941c1eb22b2d720e5af5691165">
                <text>Saha</text>
            </label>
            <label key="dddfc7ccd2f330bb0339119c9ace7ca7">
                <text>To prevent the water freezing in the pipes, we should add salt to the water to lower its freezing point.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="3d4fc630bc101c9dfb03dced8d71cc0c">
                <text>Should salt be added to ice stupas as Saha suggested?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="93cba07454f06a4a960172bbd6e2a435">
                <text>Yes</text>
            </label>
            <label key="bafd7322c6e97d25b6299b5d6fe8920b">
                <text>No</text>
            </label>
            <label key="4fd72ad9efa6be34b8ac1f513e76dfb5">
                <text>Explain your answer.</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i639a4b694f54f14615ee4e5b5fdc71589d">
            <label key="dff418d7b1d847e633a7e0bac29979d4">
                <text>Why is water sprayed over the ice stupa at night?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="169bc381c54704050903f6791fb06937">
                <text>This minimises disturbances to the villagers.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="853ef94ba79edaccbcf4bd255c7e1250">
                <text>Water is cheaper to pump at night.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="56fe26f5effa0b341b219272c40582fe">
                <text>The temperature is cold enough at night for water to freeze.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="be4db92efdcfc01e46437403b52bffa7">
                <text>This allows the water to flow more easily from the glacier to the ice stupa.</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i639a4b7c5c1bb45837df3d573c905f662a">
            <label key="66ae99239f6ef9dc7a093001b00582fa">
                <text>Which one of the following characteristics of the ice stupa would cause the ice to melt slowly?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="f36dd53b0334a4584dc2f48cad60ad89">
                <text>The ice stupa is small.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="b4c87bdfab0180500208e54ec70917f3">
                <text>The ice stupa forms from glacial melt water.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="1bed889fe1fbf1086c81150e58e77b65">
                <text>The ice stupa has a small surface-area-to-volume ratio.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="9c8828bf31051f70dca5ef7dad8f1edd">
                <text>The ice stupa is lower than the glacier.</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i639a4b873accb1462664f547ac7f8cef9f">
            <label key="f871f191d5d00b91bf7a774918156621">
                <text>Scientists conducted an investigation to determine the measures that could prevent water from freezing in metal pipes during cold weather.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="476e603360b72e1158a551b6244e7384">
                <text>Which of these actions are most likely to prevent water freezing in metal pipes?</text>
            </label>
            <label key="89b1c1de80f35eb0f385836481797561">
                <text>Select all correct answers.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="be81c4091ce688fdf0b4712b5e794101">
                <text>burying the pipe</text>
            </label>
            <label key="55a280bcba6d59ba7fe625b0779a5338">
                <text>insulating the pipe</text>
            </label>
            <label key="d5ddfac5d78e8ffa3e2f26f859f783ee">
                <text>reducing the diameter of the pipe</text>
            </label>
            <label key="1346f7b8db3f8d4c40e3571b58443765">
                <text>using a light-reflective material to make the pipe</text>
            </label>
        </item>
        <item id="i639a4b89a3d0b4593428aba6e5f040d8d9">
            <label key="1abeed5b60f7d9289daed627f4580dfe">
                <text>Ladakh is in the Himalayan mountains in India.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="c26cbf6e0039b0b41c695943e77b3b3f">
                <text>A similar artificial glacier project exists in the Andes Mountains in Chile, South America.</text>
            </label>
            <label key="17aafe8526b4e8edd1569dd014f5a943">
                <text>Cajon del Maipo, Chile</text>
            </label>
            <label key="e2911ec08a39e867d5b0f6389b1fec78">
                <text>Ladakh, India</text>
            </label>
            <label key="e9b96270ac46e5d843ed269f85d2130b">
                <text>In what month would ice stupas form in Chile? </text>
            </label>
            <label key="fa3e5edac607a88d8fd7ecb9d6d67424">
                <text>March</text>
            </label>
            <label key="688937ccaf2a2b0c45a1c9bbba09698d">
                <text>June</text>
            </label>
            <label key="cc5d90569e1c8313c2b1c2aab1401174">
                <text>September</text>
            </label>
            <label key="82331503174acbae012b2004f6431fa5">
                <text>December</text>
            </label>
        </item>
    </items>
